    "id": 10,
    "slug": "how-much-can-i-borrow-from-hustler-fund",
    "title": "How Much Can I Borrow from Hustler Fund?",
    "content": "<p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> The Hustler Fund personal loan lends from KES 100 up to KES 50,000. First-time and early limits are small, and they grow as you borrow and repay on time. There are also a group product (up to KES 1 million for eligible registered groups) and a bridge product (up to three times your assessed personal limit). The personal loan charges 8% per year, prorated daily, over an initial 14-day term.</p> <h2>Your personal limit</h2> <p>The personal product ranges from KES 100 to KES 50,000, but your own limit is set individually and starts low. It rises with a history of borrowing and repaying on time, so consistent repayment is the way to unlock more. Of each disbursement, 95% goes to your wallet and 5% to a savings account in your name, which is not a fee.</p> <table> <thead><tr><th>Product</th><th>Limit</th><th>Term</th></tr></thead> <tbody> <tr><td>Personal loan</td><td>KES 100 to KES 50,000</td><td>14 days</td></tr> <tr><td>Bridge loan</td><td>Up to 3x your personal limit</td><td>30 days</td></tr> <tr><td>Group loan</td><td>Up to KES 1 million</td><td>About 30 days</td></tr> </tbody> </table> <h2>How to increase it</h2> <p>Borrow and repay on time, repay before the 14-day term ends, and use the fund regularly. The bridge loan can give up to three times your assessed personal limit, and registered groups can access the larger group product. For more on raising your cap see <a href=\"/blog/what-is-the-maximum-hustler-fund-limit\">the maximum Hustler Fund limit</a>.</p> <h2>The cost of borrowing</h2> <p>The personal loan charges 8% per year, prorated daily, so you only pay for the days you borrow, rising to 9.5% a year if you miss the 14-day term. That makes it one of the cheapest options in Kenya, as our guide to <a href=\"/blog/which-loan-app-has-the-lowest-interest-rate-in-kenya\">the lowest-rate loan apps</a> shows. Compare it with M-Shwari in <a href=\"/blog/which-is-cheaper-hustler-fund-or-m-shwari\">Hustler Fund vs M-Shwari</a>.</p> <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2> <h3>How much can I borrow from the Hustler Fund?</h3> <p>The personal loan runs from KES 100 to KES 50,000, with your own limit starting small and growing as you repay on time. Group loans reach up to KES 1 million.</p> <h3>How do I increase my Hustler Fund limit?</h3> <p>Borrow and repay on time and use the fund regularly. The bridge product can offer up to three times your assessed personal limit.</p> <h3>What does the Hustler Fund cost?</h3> <p>8% per year on the personal loan, prorated daily over a 14-day term, rising to 9.5% a year if you repay late.</p>",
    "excerpt": "The Hustler Fund personal loan lends KES 100 to KES 50,000, with your limit starting low and rising as you repay on time. The bridge product offers up to three times your assessed limit, and group loans up to KES 1 million. It charges 8% a year, prorated daily, over a 14-day term.",
    "metaTitle": "Hustler Fund Borrowing Limits: KSh 500 to 50K Guide",
    "metaDescription": "How much can I borrow from the Hustler Fund? The personal loan runs KES 100 to KES 50,000, growing with on-time repayment; the bridge loan up to 3x your limit and group loans up to KES 1 million. It charges 8% a year prorated daily.",
    "category": "Loan Guides",
