    "title": "How Do I Pay Back Fuliza Early?",
    "content": "<p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> Fuliza repays itself automatically. The moment money comes into your M-Pesa, a deposit at an agent, a payment received, or a transfer from your bank, Fuliza deducts the outstanding amount first before the rest reaches your balance. So to clear it early, simply move money into your M-Pesa and the overdraft is settled. Check what you owe any time on *334#.</p> <h2>There is no separate repay button</h2> <p>Unlike an app loan you pay back manually, Fuliza is an overdraft that recovers itself from your incoming M-Pesa funds. You do not send a payment to a paybill, you just need money to land in your M-Pesa wallet. As soon as it does, Fuliza takes what you owe, including the daily maintenance fee accrued so far, and leaves the rest for you.</p> <h2>How to clear Fuliza early, step by step</h2> <ul> <li>Check what you owe by dialling *334#, selecting Fuliza, then Fuliza balance.</li> <li>Put money into your M-Pesa: deposit at an agent, move funds from your bank, or receive a payment.</li> <li>Fuliza automatically deducts the outstanding amount plus fees the instant the money arrives.</li> <li>Confirm the balance is cleared on *334# so no further daily fee accrues.</li> </ul> <h2>Why clearing early matters</h2> <p>Fuliza charges a daily maintenance fee for each day the balance is unpaid, so the sooner you clear it, the less it costs. On amounts up to KES 1,000 repaid within three days the daily fee is waived entirely, as our guide to <a href=\"/blog/how-much-does-fuliza-charge-per-day\">how much Fuliza charges per day</a> explains. Even partial deposits help, because Fuliza recovers part of the debt and the daily fee is then worked out on the smaller remaining balance.</p> <h2>Partial repayment is fine</h2> <p>If money comes in that is less than your full Fuliza debt, Fuliza takes all of it toward the overdraft and your usable balance stays at zero until the debt clears. That is normal, it is the service recovering what it can. Keep topping up your M-Pesa and the balance falls each time until it reaches zero.</p> <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2> <h3>How do I pay back Fuliza early?</h3> <p>Put money into your M-Pesa, by depositing at an agent, moving funds from your bank, or receiving a payment, and Fuliza automatically deducts the outstanding amount. There is no separate repayment step. Check the balance on *334#.</p> <h3>Is there a paybill to repay Fuliza?</h3> <p>No. Fuliza is recovered automatically from money entering your M-Pesa, so you do not pay a paybill. Just make sure funds reach your M-Pesa wallet.</p> <h3>Does repaying Fuliza early reduce the cost?</h3> <p>Yes. The daily maintenance fee applies for each day the balance is unpaid, so clearing it early stops further fees. Amounts up to KES 1,000 repaid within three days carry no daily fee at all.</p> <h3>Can I repay Fuliza in instalments?</h3> <p>Effectively yes. Any money entering your M-Pesa goes toward the overdraft first, so several smaller deposits clear it bit by bit, with the daily fee worked out on the shrinking balance.</p>",
    "excerpt": "Fuliza repays itself automatically: the moment money enters your M-Pesa, the overdraft is deducted first. To clear it early, move money into your M-Pesa and check the balance on *334#. There is no paybill or manual repay step.",
