    "content": "<p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> For an unexpected medical bill in Kenya, the quickest low-cost options are the M-Pesa products: Fuliza for a small gap, M-Shwari or KCB M-Pesa for a one-month loan, and the Hustler Fund for the lowest rate at 8% a year. App lenders like Tala and Branch pay out fast but cost more. Check first whether your health cover or the hospital's payment plan can reduce what you need to borrow, then borrow only what you can repay on time.</p> <h2>Before you borrow</h2> <p>A loan is not always the first answer to a medical cost. Check whether the bill is covered by your health insurance or the Social Health Authority, and ask the hospital about a payment plan, before taking on debt. If you still need cash quickly, size the loan to what you can clear on time so a one-off bill does not become a lasting debt.</p> <h2>The low-cost options first</h2> <ul> <li><strong>Fuliza</strong> for a small shortfall: a one-off 1% access fee plus a flat daily maintenance fee, free on amounts up to KES 1,000 repaid within three days, detailed in our guide to <a href=\"/blog/how-much-does-fuliza-charge-per-day\">Fuliza's daily charges</a>.</li> <li><strong>Hustler Fund</strong> at 8% a year, the cheapest, with personal limits from KES 100 to KES 50,000.</li> <li><strong>M-Shwari</strong> at a one-off 9% for 30 days and <strong>KCB M-Pesa</strong> at 7.35% (about 8.82% with excise) for a one-month loan.</li> </ul> <h2>Faster apps, higher cost</h2> <p>Tala (daily interest about 0.3% to 0.6%, up to KES 50,000) and Branch (monthly interest about 2% to 18%) disburse within minutes and can lend more, but they cost more than the M-Pesa products and add charges such as excise duty. Use them only if you will repay promptly, and read the in-app offer for the full cost, as our guide to <a href=\"/blog/what-are-the-hidden-fees-in-loan-apps-kenya\">hidden loan-app fees</a> explains.</p> <h2>Keep the cost down</h2> <p>Compare the total you will repay, not the headline rate, with our <a href=\"/total-cost-calculator/\">total cost calculator</a>, and repay on time to avoid a CRB listing. For the cheapest option overall, see <a href=\"/blog/which-loan-app-has-the-lowest-interest-rate-in-kenya\">which loan app has the lowest interest rate</a>.</p> <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2> <h3>What is the best loan for a medical emergency in Kenya?</h3> <p>The M-Pesa products you already qualify for are usually cheapest and fastest: Fuliza for a small gap, M-Shwari or KCB M-Pesa for a one-month loan, and the Hustler Fund for the lowest rate. Check insurance and a hospital payment plan first.</p> <h3>What is the cheapest emergency loan?</h3> <p>The Hustler Fund at 8% a year. A short Fuliza overdraft is free on amounts up to KES 1,000 repaid within three days, apart from the 1% access fee.</p> <h3>How fast can I get the money?</h3> <p>Most licensed apps disburse to M-Pesa within minutes once approved, though your existing limit caps how much you can take.</p>",
